cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper deals with inference and learning in high dimensional complex models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of MAP perturbations is also a common technique in these fields. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves measure concentration inequalities, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and probability theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on sequential sampling strategies may also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
